**Step 2: Implement Multi-Day Event Bars**

This is the most complex change - requires redesigning how multi-day events are rendered.

**Current approach:** Each day cell shows event text with arrows
**New approach:** Render multi-day events as absolute-positioned bars spanning columns

```tsx
// NEW: Add multi-day event bar rendering BEFORE the day cells grid

// Calculate multi-day event bars
const multiDayEventBars = useMemo(() => {
  const bars: {
    event: CalendarEvent;
    startCol: number;  // 1-7 (day of week)
    endCol: number;    // 1-7
    row: number;       // 1-5 (week of month)
    dateKey: string;
  }[] = [];

  dayCells.forEach((cell, index) => {
    const dateKey = format(cell.date, 'yyyy-MM-dd');
    const dayEvents = events[dateKey] || [];

    dayEvents.forEach((event) => {
      // Only process first occurrence of multi-day event
      if (event._isMultiDayPart && event._isMultiDayFirst) {
        const startCol = (index % 7) + 1;  // 1-7
        const row = Math.floor(index / 7) + 1;  // 1-5

        // Find end column (how many days it spans)
        let endCol = startCol;
        let checkIndex = index + 1;
        while (checkIndex < dayCells.length && checkIndex % 7 !== 0) {
          const checkDateKey = format(dayCells[checkIndex].date, 'yyyy-MM-dd');
          const checkEvents = events[checkDateKey] || [];
          if (checkEvents.find(e => e.id === event.id)) {
            endCol++;
            if (event._isMultiDayLast) break;
          } else {
            break;
          }
          checkIndex++;
        }

        bars.push({ event, startCol, endCol, row, dateKey });
      }
    });
  });

  return bars;
}, [dayCells, events]);

// RENDER: Multi-day event bars layer (absolute positioned)
<div className="relative">
  {/* Multi-day event bars */}
  {multiDayEventBars.map(({ event, startCol, endCol, row, dateKey }) => (
    <div
      key={`${event.id}-${dateKey}`}
      className="absolute h-5 px-2 rounded-sm bg-accent-magenta/20 dark:bg-accent-magenta/30 border-l-2 border-accent-magenta text-xs text-accent-magenta font-medium flex items-center truncate cursor-pointer hover:bg-accent-magenta/30 dark:hover:bg-accent-magenta/40 transition-colors"
      style={{
        gridColumnStart: startCol,
        gridColumnEnd: endCol + 1,
        gridRowStart: row,
        top: `${(row - 1) * 120 + 30}px`,  // Position below day number
        left: `calc(${((startCol - 1) / 7) * 100}% + 2px)`,
        width: `calc(${((endCol - startCol + 1) / 7) * 100}% - 4px)`,
      }}
      onClick={() => handleEventClick(event, dateKey)}
    >
      {event.title}
    </div>
  ))}

  {/* Day cells grid */}
  <div className="grid grid-cols-7 grid-rows-5 gap-px">
    {dayCells.map((cell, index) => {
      // ... existing day cell rendering
      // REMOVE multi-day event text rendering (lines 1012-1033)
      // Keep only single-day events in day cells
    })}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Alternative (Simpler):** Use CSS Grid instead of absolute positioning
- Render multi-day events as grid items with `grid-column: span N`
- Requires restructuring the day cells to allow interleaved event bars

