- [ ] Remove old multi-day text rendering
- [ ] Add hover states and click handlers
- [ ] Test with overlapping events
- [ ] Test events spanning weeks
- [ ] Verify alignment with day columns

---

## Lessons Learned

1. **Color System:** Non-existent Tailwind classes fail silently (no errors, just invisible elements) - always use semantic tokens defined in CLAUDE.md
2. **Navigation:** View-mode-specific navigation significantly improves UX - users expect Prev/Next to match current view
3. **Frozen Headers:** Flexbox `flex-1 overflow-y-auto` pattern works perfectly for Excel-like frozen rows - simpler than sticky positioning with height calculations
4. **Surgical Fixes:** Fixing 6 focused issues took less time than estimated - breaking complex tasks into atomic changes improves efficiency
5. **Deferred Complexity:** Deferring multi-day bars to separate task prevented scope creep and allowed shipping 85% of improvements quickly

---

## Success Metrics

| Issue | Status | Impact |
|-------|--------|--------|
| Dark/Light Mode Visibility | ✅ FIXED | Critical - users can now use Calendar in both modes |
| Navigation Broken | ✅ FIXED | Critical - users can now navigate days/weeks/months |
| Column Gaps | ✅ FIXED | High - Calendar looks more professional |
| Widget Controls | ✅ FIXED | Medium - cleaner UI on Calendar page |
| Day View Indicator | ✅ FIXED | Medium - users can see which day they're viewing |
| List View Scrolling | ✅ FIXED | High - users can now see all events with proper scrolling |
| Multi-Day Event Bars | ⏸️ DEFERRED | Medium - UX enhancement, not blocking |

**Overall:** 6 of 7 issues fixed (85% complete), all critical and high-priority issues resolved.

---

**Next Steps:** Create separate task for multi-day event bars implementation (estimated 45-75 min)

**Created:** November 17, 2025

